    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lord</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Buenos Ayres</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 200.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 191, of June 3 last, I have
                    the honor to inform you that on Sunday, August 24, an official Te Deum was
                    celebrated in the cathedial of this city in commemoration of the signing by
                    Chile and by the Argentine Republic of the peace agreements therein referred to.
                    The Argentine war ship <hi rend="italic">San Martin</hi> left yesterday the port
                    of Bahia Blanca en route for Chile with the purpose of effecting the exchange of
                    ratifications.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. P. Lord</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
